{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d7e09c43-75f9-47e6-893e-375660b4114c","content":"In your `App.xaml.cs`, override `CreateWindow` and subscribe to the lifecycle events on the returned `Window`:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);\n\n    window.Created       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Created\");\n    window.Activated     += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Activated\");\n    window.Deactivated   += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Deactivated\");\n    window.Stopped       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Stopped\");\n    window.Resumed       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Resumed\");\n    window.Destroying    += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Destroying\");\n    window.Backgrounding += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Backgrounding\");\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Typical transition order:**\n\n| Scenario | Events |\n|---|---|\n| App launch | `Created → Activated` |\n| Backgrounded | `Deactivated → Stopped` |\n| Resumed | `Resumed → Activated` |\n| Closed | `Deactivated → Stopped → Destroying` |\n\n> `Backgrounding` is **iOS/Mac Catalyst only** — use it to save state before suspension. On Android/Windows it won't fire.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"83b5369b-8c40-4acd-a6a8-02dd61e584e8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI Window lifecycle events and how to subscribe to them for logging/debugging. This is a general knowledge question - I can answer it directly without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":406,"requestId":"981F:30FF5A:154A1F5:17DBF0B:6A051E77"},"id":"4b332030-7e16-445a-a13e-87e58af6c54e","timestamp":"2026-05-14T00:59:44.045Z","parentId":"ada79dce-4d59-4607-aa13-0d230ee24142"}
